<br>
Game 1 is the EXP grind, small group, and solo game.  Everyone below 60 plays this game.  This game is ruled by the versatile.  Paladins, Shadowknights, Necromancers and Beastlords are champs for playing this game.<br>
<br>
Game 2 is the post-60 game.  It involves killing big things with scores of people.  For that game, Warriors and Clerics are all that matter with maybe 1 or 2 Monks, Shamans, Wizards, and Enchanters(and one mage) to help with setup/buffing.<br>
<br>
EQ was designed around game 1.  They started *trying* to create a game 2 in Kunark (Trak,VS, VPeak), and by Velious they had game 2 patched into everquest.  They added Game 2 outta demand, there was no planning or balancing from day one.  Now they "patch" things up here and there, but seem content to leave Game 2 alone. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6312>Xilr Gnomegobbler</a><BR>
Ogre Gravelord<BR>
