<br>
I've seen a beastlord pet break a mez...and then tank the god damn thing needing only one celestial heal from my cleric.  This was a Skele Lookout in Kanors, not the toughest thing in the world but pretty difficult for my ranger to tank.  That impressed me.<br>
<br>
Beastlords are a hybrid, and as such you will not be in as demand as the cornerstone focused classes when it's time to play the big game.  Your meele is not on par with a Warrior, unless the warrior is weilding a wurmslayer at level 50 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .  However, I would not sneeze at meele damage, a pet that can actually freaking tank and do damage, slow, haste, and those little buffs in my exp group. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=73211>Manas Pineblade</a><br>
Ranger of Tunare<br>Black Death Legion</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umanaspineblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Manas Pineblade</A> at: 4/9/02 11:59:26 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ubquietndrive.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BQuietNDrive</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(4/9/02 12:05:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1101.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: beastlord (usefullness)</span><hr size=1> It's good to see some support out there.<br>
We are hybrids.  I went into EQ with no real knowledge of the game, but a full awareness from friends that I would not be the cornerstone of a raid.<br>
I play a beastlord cuz it's a blast.  I dare anyone to say otherwise.  I can solo with the best of them, on level, and my gear is very mediocre in some key areas.<br>
If someone doesn't want me in a group cuz I don't have a clear role, their loss.  I wouldn't want to group with them anyway.  This does tend to be a problem with some of the veteran EQ players.  They see no real purpose in the Beastlord and often overlook us when hand picking their AA groups.  Again, their loss.  My warder's bailed even a top notch group out on more than one occasion.<br>
As long as I'm having fun with my class, that's all that matters. <p><table width="500" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#000000"><tr><td width="110"><img src="http://www.sofeq.com/sofburn.gif" width="110" height="96"></td><td width="390"><font size=4> </font><a href=" http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105982" target="_blank"><font face="verdana" color="white" size="4">Mahes</font></a><br><b><font size="4"> </font><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Level 54 Vah Shir Beastlord</font></b><br><font size="4"> </font><a href="http://www.sofeq.com" target="_blank"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="#FF0000"><b>Spirits of Fire</b></font></a></font><BR><font face=verdana size=1><I> "That which you fear the most could lead you halfway."</i></font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ubloodcelt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BloodCelt</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/bloodcelt/pics/forum/shocker.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#333333>(4/9/02 12:36:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1101.topic&index=26>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://mywebpages.comcast.net/bloodcelt/pics/forum/ezbc.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: beastlord (usefullness)</span><hr size=1> most fun I have ever had in this game was a party of four 25ish level beastlords, one necro and one druid grouped in paw.<br>
